<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658060>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figures 56–66. Pleuroxus hardingi sp. nov., parthenogenetic female from pools of the bofedal system in the cordillera del Tunari near the city of Cochabamba, State of Carrasco, Bolivia. (56) Large adult, holotype, lateral view. (57) Head. (58) Head shield, dorsal view. (59, 60) Setae at ventral margin of valve. (61, 62) Postero-ventral portion of valve. (63) Postabdomen of adult. (64, 65) Its distal portion. (66) Postabdomen of juvenile. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4658060/files/figure.png" .
